/*******************************************************
 * File: 03_SignIn.html
 * Author:
 * Co-Author(s):
 * Project: AutoTune
 *
 * Description:
 * This file sets up the basic HTML structure for the AutoTune user 
 * sign-in page. It includes social media sign-in buttons, 
 * a login form for email and password, and links for new users to 
 * sign up and existing users to recover their account.
 * 
 * Major Components:
 * - Social Sign-In Buttons: Links to Google, Apple, and Facebook login pages
 * - Email and Password Form: Allows users to sign in with their email and password
 * - Sign-Up and Forgot Password Links: Links to sign up page and forgot password page
 *
 * Usage Notes:
 * - Ensure that "style.css" and "css/main.css" are available and linked correctly 
 *   for styling to render properly.
 * - The form currently does not have an `action` attribute, so it does not submit data anywhere.
 *
 * Revision History:
 * - 2024-10-09: Initial creation
 * - 
 * 
 *******************************************************/

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <!-- Meta information for character encoding and responsive design -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SignIn</title>

    <!-- Link to external CSS files -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Main heading for the AutoTune application -->
    <h1>AutoTune</h1>

